Cap
===

 Welcome to Cap's documentation.


What is Cap ?
=============

 Cap is virtual environment manager for programmer's snippet codes.
 Cap is quick and clean on your file system.


Install
=======

How to install of Cap.


UNIX
----

    $ git clone https://github.com/narupo/cap
    $ cd cap
    $ make init && make
    $ ./build/cap -h


Windows
-------

 Using MinGW's make.

    $ git clone https://github.com/narupo/cap
    $ cd cap
    $ mingw32-make init && mingw32-make
    $ ./build/cap -h    


Example
=======

 Set your home directory. That is origin of position of virtual environment.

    $ cap home
    $ cap home /my/snippet/file/directory

 Check current environment.

    $ cap pwd

 Check current environment files.

    $ cap ls
 
 Get file content.

    $ cap cat myfile

 Change environment.

    $ cap cd next/env

 Run script.

    $ cap run bin/hello_world.py


Resource file
=============

 Cap is supported resource file with Cap's template language.
 You should be create '.caprc' at home directory or current directory and write 
the following.

    {@
        import config
        import alias

        config.set("editor", "subl")

        alias.set("hw", "run hello_world.py")
        alias.set("banana", "cat banana.txt")
    @}
